diff:1194796757:1194742528:=1,20c1,9%0a%3c This guide discusses the Small Fleet Doctrine.%0a%3c [[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeune_Ecole|Historically]], the Small%0a%3c Fleet Doctrine was developed by the French to counter the naval%0a%3c supremacy of the Britsh Royal Navy. Rather than focus on capital ships.%0a%3c the French devised a solution wherein Escort ships could be used.%0a%3c %0a%3c There are two dominant fleet doctrines in Astro Empires: Balanced and%0a%3c Efficient. The primary one is balanced, which mandates a balanced ratio%0a%3c of each unit in the fleet. The Efficient Doctrine is similar, but it%0a%3c looks at the relative efficiency of units in suggesting which units to%0a%3c add to your fleets. Ironically, the Efficient Fleet Doctrine demurs in%0a%3c the use of capital ships; much like the French Small Fleet Doctrine.%0a%3c %0a%3c Therefore, this guide honors the naval heritage of a doctrine that%0a%3c advocates for more efficient, smaller units and labels it the Small%0a%3c Fleet Doctrine. At its core, AE is still a rock-paper-scissors game.%0a%3c Build your fleet in a way that will more likely counter your opponent's%0a%3c fleet. Throughout this guide, ``efficient" describes the%0a%3c cost-effectiveness of a unit compared to other units.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> This guide discusses the Efficient Fleet Doctrine. In Astro Empires,%0a> there are two central fleet doctrines: Balanced and Efficient. The%0a> predominate doctrine is Balanced, which essentially means you have a%0a> fixed percentage of each different unit type in the fleet. The Efficient%0a> Fleet Doctrine looks at fleet composition from a cost-efficiency%0a> perspective and advocates only using units that are cost effective.%0a> %0a> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeune_Ecole%0a> %0a24a14,21%0a> Before you start pillaging and burning you must learn somethings about%0a> your weapons and it's usage.  Throughout this guide, the term%0a>  "efficient" is used. Efficient means the damage inflicted is worth the%0a> credits spent on the unit.%0a> %0a> Remember, the only advantage the attacker has is in chosing his target.%0a> All other advantages lie with the defender.%0a> %0a28,32c25,29%0a%3c The core problem with balanced fleet doctrine is that it convinces%0a%3c people that they need to build and use ships that are unnecessary in a%0a%3c fleet.  This gives your opponents an opportunity to destroy your fleet%0a%3c more efficiently. Balance is important. However, building units merely%0a%3c to create balance means you will spend too much to build a fleet. Your%0a---%0a> One problem with balanced fleet doctrine is that it convinces people%0a> that they need to build and use ships that are unnecessary in a fleet.%0a> This gives your opponents an opportunity to destroy your fleet more%0a> efficiently. Balance is important. However, building units merely to%0a> create balance means you will spend too much to build a fleet. Your%0a34,36c31,49%0a%3c Pyrric victory. In this Section, we discuss each unit and their role in%0a%3c an efficient fleet. This precedes a short set of points to remember.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Pyrric victory. In General Unit Advice, we discuss each unit and their%0a> role in an efficient fleet. This precedes a short set of points to%0a> remember.%0a> %0a> || cellspacing=0 class=structure%0a> ||             ||! Anti-Support ||! Anti-Escort ||! Anti-Capital ||%0a> || Fighter     ||    Superb     ||    Poor      ||               ||%0a> || Bomber      ||               ||    Fair      ||               ||%0a> || H.Bomber    ||               ||    Good      ||               ||%0a> || Corvette    ||               ||              ||               ||%0a> || Destroyer   ||               ||   Great      ||               ||%0a> || Cruiser     ||               ||   Superb     ||               ||%0a> || H.Cruiser   ||               ||    Good      ||    Superb     ||%0a> || Battleship  ||               ||    Fair      || Best (Levi+)  ||%0a> || Dreadnought ||       