emely handy because they are extremely fast. Using them%0a> in a battle fleet is generally optional.  They can be used as meat with%0a> the same efficiency as bombers, but they are too useful in their other%0a> applications to waste them as meat when you don't have to. A good%0a> tactice is to keep Corvette fleets of 500 or so at jumpgates for%0a> Recycler hunting and/or reinforcement of damaged fleets that are almost%0a> out of Fighters. They are fast enough to make excellent raiders, and that%0a> speed also makes them great to use as emergency meat. Fighters are twice%0a> as efficient, but if you don't have enough and you've got a fleet that's%0a> about to get hit, get your Corvettes there instead.%0a
