uiser to Heavy%0a> Cruiser when facing super-capital %0a> ships.(:footnote Before the October change, veterans referred to super-capital ships as debris in a can because smaller capital ships could more-efficiently destroy them:)%0a> %0a> Heavy Cruisers lose effectiveness against Titan-Leviathans and are%0a> worthless against DeathStars Battleships are becoming more useful as%0a> Capitol Ship Shield Penetrators.  Although it may be less profitable .%0a> However, one veteran states that a HC can still do everything else a BS%0a> can do with ''much'' more efficiency. %0a> %0a> The only noteworthy change in the use of BS is against DSs. Since HCs become%0a> totally obsolete in anti DS role (and more inefficient in the anti Levi%0a> role), we may see more BSs produced for anti capital ship operations. %0a> %0a249,264c269,293%0a%3c %25color=#C35617%25'''Consider this unit.'''%25%25 %0a%3c As ships get larger, they tend to become less efficient. %0a%3c They are significantly efficient against support units, able to destroy%0a%3c more than 12 times their value in Fighters and Heavy Bombers.%0a%3c They are inefficient against escort ships. %0a%3c Therefore, use Battleships to destroy support fleet in coordination with%0a%3c Cruisers and Heavy Cruisers.%0a%3c %0a%3c In an anti-capital role, Battleships are grossly inefficient. %0a%3c They are balanced against Dreadnoughts. %0a%3c They are less efficient than Heavy Cruisers against Titans%0a%3c They are the most efficient escort ship for killing Leviathans (but%0a%3c still require nearly three times the fleet).%0a%3c They are very efficient against Death Stars%0a%3c Therefore, do not use Battleships in an anti-capital role unless you are%0a%3c faced with Leviathans and Death Stars.%0a---%0a> One disappointing observation is that as ships get bigger in Astro%0a> Empires, the less efficient they become. Every ship is vulnerable to%0a> smaller ships. That holds true for Battleships as well. The efficiency%0a> differential from HCs to BBs is huge. Most people have far too many%0a> Battleships than they need. %0a> %0a> Battleships were a stepping-stone ship. It uses a weapon that does not%0a> affect any of the other fleet mainstays. It has shields that cannot%0a> handle Cruiser fire (so every big ship in the game hurts it). It is less%0a> efficient than Cruisers or Heavy %0a> Cruisers.(:footnote [[http://forum.astroempires.com/viewtopic.php?p=360488]]:)%0a> This stepping-stone quality is magnfied by Battleships having a%0a> different weapon type than the remainder of an efficient fleet.%0a> %0a> However, Battleships have their uses. For%0a> taking out Levis and Death Stars, this is the most efficient ship.%0a> Battleships are also ''immune'' to Fighters, making them a good ship for%0a> taking out weakly defended planets or for holding an occupation.%0a> Battleships are poor ships to include in most battle fleets due to their%0a> terrible inefficiency against Cruisers/HCs (which is what most enemy%0a> fleets are built around).%0a> %0a> Some suggest that the October 2007 changes make HCs the new Cruisers,%0a> and Battleships the new HCs. That is because 5 BS will now take 1 LV.%0a> %0a
